## BIBLIOGRAPHY WORKFLOW

### Master Bibliography Management

1. **Collection**: All citations stored in `citations/master_citations.bib`
   organized by section with category tags and priority flags.

2. **Filtering**: Three venue-specific bibliographies created:
   - `arxiv_ftqc.bib` → 120+ entries, comprehensive coverage
   - `prx_ftqc.bib` → Exactly 75 high-impact entries
   - `optica_ftqc.bib` → 60-70 photonics-focused entries

3. **Validation**: Before compilation, verify:
   - No duplicate entry keys
   - All entries have required fields (author, title, year)
   - DOIs and ArXiv IDs formatted correctly
   - Author names consistent across entries
   - PRX has exactly 75 references (not 74, not 76)

### BibTeX Entry Requirements

**Minimal valid entry:**
```bibtex
@article{AuthorYear,
  author  = {Last, First and Last2, First2},
  title   = {Paper Title},
  journal = {Journal Name},
  volume  = {XX},
  pages   = {YYY--ZZZ},
  year    = {YYYY},
  doi     = {10.XXXX/YYYYY}
}
```

**For ArXiv preprints:**
```bibtex
@misc{AuthorYear,
  author = {Last, First},
  title  = {Preprint Title},
  year   = {YYYY},
  eprint = {YYMM.NNNNN},
  archivePrefix = {arXiv},
  primaryClass  = {quant-ph}
}
```

