## VENUE-SPECIFIC NOTES

### arXiv (quant-ph)
- No page limits, comprehensive coverage encouraged
- Include all 10 figures from `figures/` directory
- Bibliography via external `arxiv_ftqc.bib` file + bibtex compilation
- Appendices allowed and recommended for detailed proofs
- Target audience: Broad quantum computing research community

### Physical Review X (PRX)
- Strict 12-page limit including figures and references
- Maximum 4 figures (select most impactful from `figures/`)
- Exactly 75 references in `prx_ftqc.bib` (no more, no less)
- External bibliography file with bibtex compilation
- Single-column format during submission
- High-impact journals preferred (Nature, Science, PRL, PRX, RMP)

### Optica
- 10-page limit
- Photonics-focused content and citations
- 60-70 references in `optica_ftqc.bib`, emphasizing:
  - Photonic band engineering
  - Femtosecond laser fabrication
  - Optical implementations of quantum systems
- External bibliography file with bibtex compilation
- Experimental emphasis over pure theory
- Target audience: Optics and photonics community

## SUCCESS CRITERIA

A successful compilation session produces:
1. Zero LaTeX errors in .log file
2. All citations resolved (no ?? marks in PDF)
3. All figures rendered correctly (check PDF visually)
4. Page count within venue limits
5. Bibliography formatted per venue style
6. No orphaned references or labels
7. Proper section numbering and cross-references
8. Reference count matches target (especially PRX = 75)

## TROUBLESHOOTING COMMON ISSUES

**"Undefined control sequence \Hilbert"**
→ Add to preamble: `\newcommand{\Hilbert}{\mathcal{H}}`

**"Cannot find Fig1_Hilbert_Scaling.png"**
→ Check that path includes `figures/` subdirectory
→ Correct: `\includegraphics{figures/Fig1_Hilbert_Scaling.png}`
→ Wrong: `\includegraphics{Fig1_Hilbert_Scaling.png}`

**"Empty bibliography"**
→ Verify `\bibliography{arxiv_ftqc}` has no .bib extension
→ Check that bibtex was run before second pdflatex
→ Ensure .bib file exists in project root

**"Too many references for PRX"**
→ PRX must have exactly 75 entries in prx_ftqc.bib
→ Use: `grep -c "^@" prx_ftqc.bib` to count entries

**"Missing $ inserted"**
→ Math mode error, check for unescaped underscores in text
→ Use `\_` for literal underscores outside math mode

**"File not found: section_ii_fractal..."**
→ If using `\input{section_ii_fractal...}`, ensure file exists
→ Or remove `\input` command if section is embedded in main file

